    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Increased Hopes For Nature Sanctuary</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Norwalk Land Trust president Marny Smith letter on April 8 article on purchase of land for Rowayton nature sanctuary in Connecticut</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thank you for ''Preservationists Scramble to Buy Vital Link to Rowayton Nature Sanctuary'' (April 8). We land trust volunteers believe we are doing the right thing by saving this ''greenbelt of shoreline, marsh and meadow on Farm Creek, an inlet off Long Island Sound.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Thank you for ''Preservationists Scramble to Buy Vital Link to Rowayton Nature Sanctuary'' (April 8). We land trust volunteers believe we are doing the right thing by saving this ''greenbelt of shoreline, marsh and meadow on Farm Creek, an inlet off Long Island Sound.''</p>
        <p>We are happy to report that the owner of the Hart property has given us a three-month extension -- to Sept. 1 -- to reach our goal of $4.3 million. We welcome visitors to the property to see for themselves what a great investment this is for nature.</p>
        <p>Marny Smith  Norwalk</p>
        <p>The writer is president, Norwalk Land Trust.</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
